text: Myconita plutelliformis is a moth in the family Gelechiidae. It was described by Snellen in 1901. It is found in India, Indonesia (Java) and Australia,Myconita at funet where it has been recorded from the Northern Territory and Queensland. The wingspan is about 10 mm. The forewings are dark brown with a broad pale stripe along the inner margin. The hindwings are pale brown.Lepidoptera Larvae of Australia ==References== Category:Moths described in 1901 Category:Dichomeridinae
title: Myconita plutelliformis
